<TITLE> MRPs, MRVs launched </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)-Prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Wednesday formally launched machine-readable passports (MRPs) and machine-readable visas (MRVs) at the Osmani Memorial Auditorium. She handed over MRPs to 14 eminent personalities including ministers, teachers, journalists, students and workers. Dhaka's passport office started receiving applications for MRPs from Apr 1. Fees applicable for the general passports are Tk 3,000 and for urgent ones Tk 6,000. It will cost between Tk 700 to Tk 800 to produce each MRP. There are currently about 1.2 crore manual passport holders in the country. According to the International Civil Aviation Organisation (ICAO), all countries should have introduced MRPs and MRVs by April 1, 2010. To try and comply with the ICAO requirement, the passport department controversially hired IRIS, a Malaysian company to produce MRP/MR
